[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Evaluating static initializers**\n\nI'm considering how to handle static initializers in generated classes. Invoking static methods can trigger the static initialization, which could lead to a `LinkageError` in Groovy tests. I’m wondering if we should catch these errors and assert them as known issues. For native execution, skipping the error isn’t allowed. If the closure class is initialized at build time in the Native Image, I need to be consistent with how we manage errors. I think using `rethrowUnlessUnsupportedNativeImageError` for `LinkageError` is the right approach.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0f727aea83dffee2016a01386c3754819d90bace5241d3913e\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqATh_p8p41iXUQE_ejgleaU0g651bX97CvVWn537oQVKJ1SHx6sliEDUBfya5NOPRFuSA95xwZ0udsIta8Lxcn-7bupnc6HKOVNhCPODcadIjyE1-zoi80PRpnjv-AqCevu49htMxMuPWTZM_QJOe_B_ylJfutOeSGG8JbrsIFTwZbc2ozHHpMa1pgjOYwls6ZO4BSv3Y_rSJqHxbjHR-YT_Rq6L6D3PKftH38nmVIWe3tRifCsCt10-uFsRbMpzkmAcrIHkBQfZtzyB91SR7h-K9IvpI_0u5ARHi6A9oYStPvJa1LDQUISY03SzB_2Z9mHVB9fxFtXWZHaJDIaYXk-DeVkRHxWAHAu3CL1yfCBH3BEvPg-xX_FUwhjnLzwrWaR4O0C11cbcTvz_1rjG1rdlBIgpUtmKpFfIvRKD-p5wEjUOtrRM-ejFt1y0-FZky1sOq-TXpRsT33RLk2IjcN7r_6vOD3LnAgffs4vqbjmxMVvoKVU6oToEkyM4OBw6Rpd3fo937GBLvukmMSoCeZpjOz8ZWw2bmBB5ppGQWwhb_V2NwHrrVLEcKrhsWHv-y-XXVR0sZV65EciZtvlPoMrg7onBecqhgQeW-bU5hfbYuVbzHkWbVwMhtuY8Idaoa9spECcbGVg0GWQCg2QWV_SWtNeXuS36RV0_mI-n9MbPBs-oEHliF7f5SVj_USItPXotRtUw4iWM4OXQ6cGubTNEBcdmaMl26OprmCJPpQnyfPTLjMgyGW5qo_FTqqZ1z0Orb666KoXCqvTj-mFpa6fqIrRdB-T2BAnKZWAxR3a14aW99qI3CHSwoANQeYjYXoQr2fP-G2vXFGBwC5YI_2C3yf44zMX1ZRDLGolT3twqcsn_7NrIxPdUAT_Xldnua-SwJaD4Y7SvFDf0rbl1Zx1YcJaib87jvMJDYALzDpFT17e7dCPwaljgbwePP3cgAFT8QHBcMLD1LxUscrAmnAu5tYezR56zQXNmakrdRsVC--Dq6FVlziPJHzAKEuxq4Oxz_awaWNWynl3BP16IzKbxmKId2EsSBztwcCGCGEvzlCbzSS7lViQcVaR5f0gpssFtixSq-vyiYnxQJGVuynAwnQxdTt5ucpnLZPuLSDPJsY26FdV7k3herC5UAeneAZ6Ah40hlln9BB